<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/formula-md3.css">

    <!-- Import Material Design Symbols (the new version of icons?) -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Material+Symbols+Outlined" rel="stylesheet" />


    <!-- From MD3 README -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <script type="importmap">
        {
        "imports": {
            "@material/web/": "https://esm.run/@material/web/"
        }
        }
    </script>
    <script type="module">
        import '@material/web/all.js';
        import {styles as typescaleStyles} from '@material/web/typography/md-typescale-styles.js';

        document.adoptedStyleSheets.push(typescaleStyles.styleSheet);
    </script>

    <script src="https://polyfill.io/v3/polyfill.min.js?features=es6"></script>
    <script id="MathJax-script" async
            src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-mml-chtml.js"></script>

    
</head>

<body>
    
    <div class="header">
        <div class="header-content">
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined roadmap-icon">close</span>
            <h1>Deriving Our Formula</h1>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="progress">
        <div class="progress-content">
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined toolbox-icon">calculate</span>
            <span class="material-symbols-outlined roadmap-icon">conversion_path</span>
            <svg class="progress-bar" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" height="10" fill="none">
                <rect width="100%" height="10" rx="5" fill="#ACB2ED"/>
            </svg>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="instruction-content">

        <div id="fd-intro">
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>In this activity, we will learn more about the formulas we can use in the Figure of Merit of a Galvanometer lab.</p>
        
            <div class="button-container">
                <md-outlined-button class="fd-next-button" data-key="next_fd_intro_toolbox">Next</md-outlined-button>
            </div>

        </div>   

        <div id="fd-goal">
            <h2>INSERT TITLE</h2>
            <p>Our goal is to find the <b>figure of merit</b> of the galvanometer, indicated by the variable <b>k</b>. </p>
            <p>If we want to find <b>k</b>, which formula should we start with?</p>
            
            <div class="mc-question">
                <md-outlined-button class="mc-button"><span>Ohm's Law: </span> \( V = IR \)</md-outlined-button>
                <md-outlined-button class="mc-button"><span>Figure of Merit: </span> \( I = k \theta \)</md-outlined-button>
                <md-outlined-button class="mc-button"><span>Series Resistance: </span> \( R_T = R_1 + R_2 \)</md-outlined-button>
            </div>

        </div>   


    </div>
    
    <!-- Import Javascript Code -->
    <script src="javascript/formula-md3.js"></script>
        
</body>

</html>